10:
Very well, imposters. I shall show thee 
the might of a TRUE dragon!
30:
You were beating your wings with 
a grim look on your face. So we 
decided to hitch a ride on your tail.
34:
And thou shalt pay for thy feckless 
curiousity with thy lives! This place—
39: Hey, look, dragons. There sure are a lot.
42:
Wretched lizards... In giving both mind 
and body over to the Serpent...
50: Alk! Get out of the way!
56: What the?! You just barbequed them!
60:
It matters not how many flies swarm 
before the flames...
63:
The fire shall consume them every 
time!
82:
Petty minds will resort to petty tricks. 
But against the great—
87:
Wait! You must not use that move 
heedlessly!
91: I do not take orders from anyone!
95:
Prominence Blaze consumes your 
strength and strains your mind. That 
much was made clear during our 
battle!
99:
What dost thou know of self-
preservation, HUSK?! No, I shall not 
listen to thee!
102:
Your hubris will be your downfall, 
Vagner!
107:
STOOOP!
What are you, an old married couple?!
110: I'LL take care of the rear? Okay?!
118:
Nuh-uh! I can take 'em!
Probably.
Not like we have any other choice.
123:
I will go with Alk.
Vagner, Stella! Hold off the enemy 
here.
128: Vagner, will you accept my help?
132:
...They are headed towards that 
labyrinth. Act as an extra pair of eyes, 
and my flames and claws shall do the 
rest.
144:
Uh... There's no end to them…
I am never stepping in during 
a couple's spat. Ever. Again.
147:
If you've strength enough for idle talk, 
you'll be fine. ...Though I once thought 
your levity would be the death of you.
150:
Ohh... I still think my big mouth could 
very much kill me.
152:
But not today!
All hail the King of Dragons!
157:
Alk! Light! Get on!
I will destroy them all from the skies!
165:
We are tyrants of the land, and of the 
air. We are the Ancients!
168:
Bow before us... or crumble to ash!
Prominence Blaze!
175:
Did you have to fling us off like 
baggage?!
178:
Be grateful I did not send thee 
plunging to thy death. Never again 
shalt thou ride on my back.
183:
Vagner. What were those dra—
I mean, those lizards?
186:
Serpents... Creatures that both are 
and are not dragons. Oath-breakers.
There are many names for them.
188:
They are our old foes... Bane of 
dragons, but irrelevant to mortals.
...Or so I had thought.
192:
"I can take them," was it?
...So eager to leap into the fray.
200:
Rejoice. Thou art now rearguard to an 
Ancient.
205:
WHAT?! Wait, no, no, no. Earlier, that 
was neccessity and the adrenaline 
talking, but NOW—
208:
I shall test the strength of thy body 
and heart. Take care not to crack in 
the heat, little one.
212:
He has more mettle than you would 
expect.
